Real estate group Pam Golding has highlighted a number of luxury properties which are currently up for sale in South Africa. Andrew Golding, chief executive of the Pam Golding properties, said that the group is beginning to see ‘encouraging resilience’ from the South African property market as the country begins to emerge from the effects of the Covid-19 pandemic. He said that both activity and sales across all price ranges was improving, with signs of increasing buoyancy in the luxury residential market too. Below are some of the properties available around R40 million. 5 bedroom house in Sandhurst, Sandton – R38 million Entrance hall with marble floors;
